(The GPL is supplied as !ZapDiff.Copying. Source should be available from
wherever you got ZapDiff or Zap; if you have difficulty, get in touch with
the maintainer, below.)

ZapDiff colours files output by diff(1) or a similar utility. It recognises
'standard' diff and unified diff automatically, and will colour control
lines, adds and removed appropriately. There's no support for context diffs,
or Acorn diff, at present.

James Aylett
dj@zap.uk.eu.org
